  "name": "Bollinger CMO Mean Reversion Strategy",
  "description": "This algorithm employs a mean-reverting strategy using Bollinger Bands and the Chande Momentum Oscillator. It initiates a long position when the price closes below the lower Bollinger Band and the CMO indicates oversold conditions with a value below -50.",
  "algorithm_type": "MeanReverting",
  "prompt": "Develop an expert-level MeanReverting trading algorithm in Python that uses a combination of Bollinger Bands (20-period SMA with 2 standard deviations) and the Chande Momentum Oscillator (CMO) over a 14-period window on 30-minute candlesticks. The strategy should enter a long position when price closes below the lower Bollinger Band and the CMO falls below -50, indicating oversold conditions, and exit when price reverts to the 20-period SMA or when CMO crosses above 0. Enter a short position when price closes above the upper Bollinger Band and the CMO rises above +50, indicating overbought conditions, exiting when price reverts to the SMA or CMO crosses below 0. Include volume confirmation by requiring volume to be above its 20-period moving average for entries. Provide clear code structure for signal generation, position management, and risk control including a fixed 1% stop-loss based on entry price.",
